    "comment": "Rationale: Over expression of EGFP-p65 allowed the investigation of the protein redistribution from the dendritic brunch to the nucleus using a FRAP approach.\nFollowing photobleaching of a dendritic segment, authors observed fluorescence recovery which was unidirectional and triggered only by NMDA application. Accordingly, photobleaching of the somatic region shows a significant recovery after NMDA application, different from the recovery observed under basal conditions.. Experimental description: Dissociated primary hippocampal cultures were prepared from postnatal P1 mice.\n\nThere is no information whatsoever about the origin of the p65 sequence they used for their clones.\n\n24/01/2018 Pim\n- Authors contacted for species information (dd 24/01/2018\n mkm@jhmi.edu). Aswer via phone: \"human\"",
